<PageLayout
  title="Cookies Policy"
  eyebrow="Privacy Hub"
  heading="Cookies Policy"
  intro="What cookies we use, why, and how to control them."
  accent="tertiary"
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1499636136210-6f4ee915583e?w=1600&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
>
  <h2>What is a cookie?</h2>
  <p>A small text file that websites store on your device to remember things — like keeping you logged in or remembering your dark mode preference.</p>

  <h2>What we use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> login, security, language. Can't be disabled.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> aggregated, anonymous usage data. Optional.</li>
    <li><strong>Preference cookies:</strong> theme, language, region. Optional.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No third-party advertising cookies.</li>
    <li>No cross-site tracking pixels.</li>
    <li>No fingerprinting.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to control cookies</h2>
  <p>You can manage your preferences anytime via the <strong>Cookie Settings</strong> link in the footer or your browser settings. Disabling essential cookies will break login.</p>
</PageLayout>
